race.description: Ladies Day Saturday 8 November Mdn Plate
race.comment: EMBALLEE (7) indicated a win was imminent after closing strongly from back in the pack with a sound third over 1400m at Randwick Kensington. Capable of sitting off the pace and rounding them up with Tommy Berry aboard. SWITZ (3) is ready to peak fourth-up and expect to see him take control early from the sticky gate. Beaten for early speed but kept coming through the line when a respectable third over 1500m at Newcastle. Shapes as a genuine top-three prospect. SILVER TEMPEST (1) well in the market at debut when he chipped away late to finish third in a small field over 1300m at Orange. Has more to offer and looking for the trip. BIG BERTHA (6) looks the pick of the rest after finding the 1300m too short at Dubbo on resumption for the new yard. Placed at the trip and expecting a stronger showing.
